{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FWdBzodbtFeKNeiQ7BPNCS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent Exploration Notes\n     2→\n     3→## Key Files & Roles\n     4→\n     5→- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for agent scripts. Provides environment defaults, output helpers, cleanup/trap setup, lock handling, and shared result formatting utilities.\n     6→- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: refactored agent using the shared library; pattern for complex scoped execution and structured output.\n     7→- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: refactored single-step and multi-step domain runner with CHANGED_FILES mapping and CI-aware format behavior.\n     8→- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: refactored agent that demonstrates formatter/linter fallbacks and scoped execution over changed files.\n     9→- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: refactored agent with optional tooling (tflint), non-mutating checks, and lock-aware sequencing.\n    10→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: central test orchestrator for shellcheck plus fixture execution.\n    11→- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: per-agent scenario fixtures; each includes `scenario.env` with `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n    12→- `install.sh`: installer entrypoint; currently installs `bash-agent`, `cargo-agent`, `go-agent`, `npm-agent`, `py-agent`, and `terra-agent`, and patches shared library for local/remote install modes.\n    13→- `README.md`: human-facing agent catalog, usage examples, and quick-start guidance.\n    14→- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI currently runs scenario slices for bash, cargo, go, npm, py, and terraform agents.\n    15→- `.ralph/specs/05-gha-agent.md`: current specification for the new gha-agent implementation.\n    16→- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: reference for required files, trigger patterns, and required helpers for each new agent.\n    17→- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: final acceptance checks for any new agent.\n    18→- `.ralph/task.md`: task-level scope and spec sequence for eight remaining agents.\n    19→- `.ralph/automation-opportunities.md`: pending candidates for automatable process improvements.\n    20→- `.ralph/lessons.jsonl`: historical manual lessons and decision points.\n    21→\n    22→## Patterns & Conventions\n    23→\n    24→- Bash scripts use Bash 3.2-compatible syntax and start with `#!/usr/bin/env bash` plus `set -euo pipefail`.\n    25→- Agents print canonical Step/Result/Time output and end with `Overall` and `Logs`.\n    26→- Every `Result: FAIL` includes a `Fix:` line; failures preserve full logs and print truncated context locally.\n    27→- Universal knobs are expected in all agents: `RUN_<STEP>`, `FAIL_FAST`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, and `CHANGED_FILES`.\n    28→- CI behavior for scripts is controlled by `CI=true|1`; line truncation is disabled and check-only mode is preferred for mutating steps.\n    29→- Scripts should parse help flags before running `need()` checks so `--help` works without project context.\n    30→- `--fail-fast` is supported in `all` mode via shared `should_continue()` guard.\n    31→- Workflow-level locking is centralized in shared helpers using `flock` with Perl fallback.\n    32→- Missing optional tooling is expected to produce `SKIP` with explicit reason; required tooling exits 2 through `need()`.\n    33→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` skips scenarios whose `REQUIRED_TOOLS` are unavailable.\n    34→\n    35→## Database Schema\n    36→\n    37→No database is used.\n    38→\n    39→## Test Infrastructure\n    40→\n    41→- Scenario discovery happens via `find tests -name scenario.env`, including `clean` and `issues` fixture pairs per agent.\n    42→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` can run all tests, a named fragment filter, `--list`, and shellcheck-only mode.\n    43→- Shellcheck is run with `--severity=warning` and is required to pass for all `*.sh` files under `skills`, `tests`, `lib`, and root installer scripts.\n    44→- Fixture assertions are exit-based using `EXPECT_EXIT`; mismatches show log slices from the failing fixture.\n    45→- Scenario fixtures declare `REQUIRED_TOOLS` and are skipped automatically when missing.\n    46→\n    47→## Architecture & Data Flow\n    48→\n    49→- Invocation enters through a script under `skills/<agent>/scripts`.\n    50→- Shared library is sourced early after env defaults and before agent-specific logic.\n    51→- On command execution: parse CLI/help/flags, validate required tools, initialize output directory and lock, resolve scope from `CHANGED_FILES`, execute selected steps, and write each step log under `$OUTDIR`.\n    52→- Steps run external tooling with scoped targets when available, write logs to `$OUTDIR/<step>.log`, and print status summaries.\n    53→- Final status is aggregated into `overall_ok` and rendered via `print_overall`.\n    54→- `install.sh` and `README.md` are the registration/discovery boundary for new agents.\n    55→- For gha-agent, the data path is `.github/workflows/*.yml|*.yaml` from the project root; no existing gha-agent implementation is currently present in repo.\n    56→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04f1945e-7bf3-4940-ab64-46803dcd06b1","uuid":"3ea1a16f-7184-42ea-a868-6741a293383e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","content":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for agent scripts. Provides environment defaults, output helpers, cleanup/trap setup, lock handling, and shared result formatting utilities.\n- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: refactored agent using the shared library; pattern for complex scoped execution and structured output.\n- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: refactored single-step and multi-step domain runner with CHANGED_FILES mapping and CI-aware format behavior.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: refactored agent that demonstrates formatter/linter fallbacks and scoped execution over changed files.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: refactored agent with optional tooling (tflint), non-mutating checks, and lock-aware sequencing.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: central test orchestrator for shellcheck plus fixture execution.\n- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: per-agent scenario fixtures; each includes `scenario.env` with `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- `install.sh`: installer entrypoint; currently installs `bash-agent`, `cargo-agent`, `go-agent`, `npm-agent`, `py-agent`, and `terra-agent`, and patches shared library for local/remote install modes.\n- `README.md`: human-facing agent catalog, usage examples, and quick-start guidance.\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI currently runs scenario slices for bash, cargo, go, npm, py, and terraform agents.\n- `.ralph/specs/05-gha-agent.md`: current specification for the new gha-agent implementation.\n- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: reference for required files, trigger patterns, and required helpers for each new agent.\n- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: final acceptance checks for any new agent.\n- `.ralph/task.md`: task-level scope and spec sequence for eight remaining agents.\n- `.ralph/automation-opportunities.md`: pending candidates for automatable process improvements.\n- `.ralph/lessons.jsonl`: historical manual lessons and decision points.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n\n- Bash scripts use Bash 3.2-compatible syntax and start with `#!/usr/bin/env bash` plus `set -euo pipefail`.\n- Agents print canonical Step/Result/Time output and end with `Overall` and `Logs`.\n- Every `Result: FAIL` includes a `Fix:` line; failures preserve full logs and print truncated context locally.\n- Universal knobs are expected in all agents: `RUN_<STEP>`, `FAIL_FAST`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, and `CHANGED_FILES`.\n- CI behavior for scripts is controlled by `CI=true|1`; line truncation is disabled and check-only mode is preferred for mutating steps.\n- Scripts should parse help flags before running `need()` checks so `--help` works without project context.\n- `--fail-fast` is supported in `all` mode via shared `should_continue()` guard.\n- Workflow-level locking is centralized in shared helpers using `flock` with Perl fallback.\n- Missing optional tooling is expected to produce `SKIP` with explicit reason; required tooling exits 2 through `need()`.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` skips scenarios whose `REQUIRED_TOOLS` are unavailable.\n\n## Database Schema\n\nNo database is used.\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- Scenario discovery happens via `find tests -name scenario.env`, including `clean` and `issues` fixture pairs per agent.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` can run all tests, a named fragment filter, `--list`, and shellcheck-only mode.\n- Shellcheck is run with `--severity=warning` and is required to pass for all `*.sh` files under `skills`, `tests`, `lib`, and root installer scripts.\n- Fixture assertions are exit-based using `EXPECT_EXIT`; mismatches show log slices from the failing fixture.\n- Scenario fixtures declare `REQUIRED_TOOLS` and are skipped automatically when missing.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n\n- Invocation enters through a script under `skills/<agent>/scripts`.\n- Shared library is sourced early after env defaults and before agent-specific logic.\n- On command execution: parse CLI/help/flags, validate required tools, initialize output directory and lock, resolve scope from `CHANGED_FILES`, execute selected steps, and write each step log under `$OUTDIR`.\n- Steps run external tooling with scoped targets when available, write logs to `$OUTDIR/<step>.log`, and print status summaries.\n- Final status is aggregated into `overall_ok` and rendered via `print_overall`.\n- `install.sh` and `README.md` are the registration/discovery boundary for new agents.\n- For gha-agent, the data path is `.github/workflows/*.yml|*.yaml` from the project root; no existing gha-agent implementation is currently present in repo.\n","numLines":56,"startLine":1,"totalLines":56}}}
