{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GCK4VWq1UNyibKwyBD59ty","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: bash-agent\n     3→description: |\n     4→  Run bash-agent.sh — a lean shell script validation runner that produces agent-friendly output.\n     5→  Use when: running shell/bash script checks (syntax, lint), verifying shell scripts before committing,\n     6→  or when the user asks to run shellcheck, bash checks, or validate shell scripts.\n     7→  Triggers on: bash agent, shell agent, shellcheck, bash lint, shell checks, verify shell scripts.\n     8→context: fork\n     9→allowed-tools:\n    10→  - Bash(scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    11→  - Bash(RUN_*=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    12→  - Bash(SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    13→  - Bash(MAX_LINES=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    14→  - Bash(KEEP_DIR=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    15→  - Bash(FAIL_FAST=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    16→  - Bash(CHANGED_FILES=* scripts/bash-agent.sh*)\n    17→---\n    18→\n    19→# Bash Agent\n    20→\n    21→Run the `bash-agent.sh` script for lean, structured shell script validation output designed for coding agents.\n    22→\n    23→## Script Location\n    24→\n    25→```\n    26→scripts/bash-agent.sh\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→## Usage\n    30→\n    31→### Run Full Suite (syntax + lint)\n    32→```bash\n    33→scripts/bash-agent.sh\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→### Run Individual Steps\n    37→```bash\n    38→scripts/bash-agent.sh syntax    # bash -n syntax check only\n    39→scripts/bash-agent.sh lint      # shellcheck lint only\n    40→scripts/bash-agent.sh all       # full suite (default)\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→## Environment Knobs\n    44→\n    45→| Variable | Default | Description |\n    46→|----------|---------|-------------|\n    47→| `RUN_SYNTAX` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip syntax check |\n    48→| `RUN_LINT` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip shellcheck lint |\n    49→| `SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY` | `warning` | shellcheck `--severity` level (`error`, `warning`, `info`, `style`) |\n    50→| `FAIL_FAST` | `0` | Set to `1` to stop after first failure (or use `--fail-fast`) |\n    51→| `CHANGED_FILES` | _(empty)_ | Space-separated changed file paths; scopes checks to those `.sh` files |\n    52→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max output lines printed per step (unlimited in CI) |\n    53→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n    54→\n    55→## Output Format\n    56→\n    57→- Each step prints a header (`Step: syntax`, `Step: lint`)\n    58→- Results are `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `SKIP`\n    59→- On failure, output is truncated to `MAX_LINES`\n    60→- Failed shellcheck results include wiki links for each error code\n    61→- Full logs are saved to a temp directory (path printed in output)\n    62→- Overall result is printed at the end: `Overall: PASS` or `Overall: FAIL`\n    63→\n    64→## Important Notes\n    65→\n    66→- The script discovers all `.sh` files recursively, excluding `.git`, `node_modules`, and `vendor`\n    67→- `CHANGED_FILES` scopes checks to only the listed `.sh` files that exist\n    68→- `SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY` controls the minimum severity level for shellcheck warnings\n    69→- In CI (`CI=true`), `MAX_LINES` defaults to unlimited; locally it defaults to 40\n    70→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HhqdySJWhuEHurAJzr5dzG","session_id":"04f1945e-7bf3-4940-ab64-46803dcd06b1","uuid":"0c45e430-e203-4e06-bcdd-83b1d6ea2ab4"}
