{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019VimRbn1879gqDYnBiLfTo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent\n     2→\n     3→Every time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n     4→\n     5→## Why?\n     6→\n     7→Standard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n     8→\n     9→- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n    10→- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n    11→- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n    12→- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n    13→\n    14→## Available Agents\n    15→\n    16→| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n    17→|-------|-----------|-------|\n    18→| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n    19→| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n    20→| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n    21→| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n    22→| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n    23→| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n    24→\n    25→## Quick Start\n    26→\n    27→### Install via curl\n    28→\n    29→```sh\n    30→curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n    31→```\n    32→\n    33→### Install from local clone\n    34→\n    35→```sh\n    36→git clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\n    37→cd x-agent\n    38→sh install.sh\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→Local installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\n    42→The installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\n    43→It also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n    44→\n    45→### Use directly (no install)\n    46→\n    47→```sh\n    48→# Rust project\n    49→path/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n    50→\n    51→# Node.js project\n    52→path/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n    53→\n    54→# Python project\n    55→path/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n    56→\n    57→# Go project\n    58→path/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n    59→\n    60→# Terraform project\n    61→path/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→## Usage\n    65→\n    66→### bash-agent\n    67→\n    68→```sh\n    69→bash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\n    70→bash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\n    71→bash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\n    72→SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→### cargo-agent\n    76→\n    77→```sh\n    78→cargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\n    79→cargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\n    80→cargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\n    81→cargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\n    82→cargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n    83→```\n    84→\n    85→### go-agent\n    86→\n    87→```sh\n    88→go-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\n    89→go-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\n    90→go-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\n    91→go-agent.sh test            # tests only\n    92→FMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n    96→\n    97→### npm-agent\n    98→\n    99→```sh\n   100→npm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\n   101→npm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   102→npm-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   103→npm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n   104→```\n   105→\n   106→npm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n   107→\n   108→### py-agent\n   109→\n   110→```sh\n   111→py-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\n   112→py-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\n   113→py-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   114→py-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   115→py-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→py-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n   119→\n   120→### terra-agent\n   121→\n   122→```sh\n   123→terra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\n   124→terra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\n   125→terra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\n   126→terra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\n   127→terra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\n   128→TERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\n   129→FMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n   130→```\n   131→\n   132→`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n   133→`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n   134→\n   135→## Environment Knobs\n   136→\n   137→All agents share the same pattern:\n   138→\n   139→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   140→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   141→| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n   142→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n   143→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n   144→\n   145→```sh\n   146→# Skip tests, keep logs\n   147→RUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n   148→\n   149→# Only run lint and typecheck\n   150→RUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n   151→```\n   152→\n   153→## Output Format\n   154→\n   155→```\n   156→------------------------------------------------------------\n   157→Step: clippy\n   158→Errors: 0\n   159→Warnings: 3\n   160→\n   161→Diagnostics (first 40 lines):\n   162→warning: unused variable `x`\n   163→warning: unused import `std::io`\n   164→warning: function `old_handler` is never used\n   165→\n   166→Result: PASS\n   167→Full JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\n   168→Lean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\n   169→Time: 4s\n   170→------------------------------------------------------------\n   171→Overall: PASS\n   172→Logs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n   173→```\n   174→\n   175→On **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n   176→\n   177→## Claude Code Skills\n   178→\n   179→The `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n   180→\n   181→- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n   182→- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n   183→- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n   184→- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n   185→- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n   186→- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n   187→\n   188→## License\n   189→\n   190→MIT\n   191→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04f1945e-7bf3-4940-ab64-46803dcd06b1","uuid":"d0d75a0f-8460-4301-9c2d-76ff0be9011b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md","content":"# x-agent\n\nEvery time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n\n## Why?\n\nStandard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n\n- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n\n## Available Agents\n\n| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n|-------|-----------|-------|\n| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Install via curl\n\n```sh\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n### Install from local clone\n\n```sh\ngit clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\ncd x-agent\nsh install.sh\n```\n\nLocal installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\nThe installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\nIt also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n\n### Use directly (no install)\n\n```sh\n# Rust project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Node.js project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n\n# Python project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n\n# Go project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n\n# Terraform project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### bash-agent\n\n```sh\nbash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\nbash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\nbash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\nSHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n```\n\n### cargo-agent\n\n```sh\ncargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\ncargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\ncargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\ncargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\ncargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n```\n\n### go-agent\n\n```sh\ngo-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\ngo-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\ngo-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\ngo-agent.sh test            # tests only\nFMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n```\n\n`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n\n### npm-agent\n\n```sh\nnpm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\nnpm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\nnpm-agent.sh test           # tests only\nnpm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n```\n\nnpm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n\n### py-agent\n\n```sh\npy-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\npy-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\npy-agent.sh lint           # lint only\npy-agent.sh test           # tests only\npy-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n```\n\npy-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n\n### terra-agent\n\n```sh\nterra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\nterra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\nterra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\nterra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\nterra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\nTERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\nFMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n```\n\n`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n\n## Environment Knobs\n\nAll agents share the same pattern:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n\n```sh\n# Skip tests, keep logs\nRUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Only run lint and typecheck\nRUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\n```\n------------------------------------------------------------\nStep: clippy\nErrors: 0\nWarnings: 3\n\nDiagnostics (first 40 lines):\nwarning: unused variable `x`\nwarning: unused import `std::io`\nwarning: function `old_handler` is never used\n\nResult: PASS\nFull JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\nLean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\nTime: 4s\n------------------------------------------------------------\nOverall: PASS\nLogs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n```\n\nOn **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n\n## Claude Code Skills\n\nThe `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n\n- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":191,"startLine":1,"totalLines":191}}}
