{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JmZSd6qtqCAMULc8QWF4mB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent Exploration Notes\n     2→\n     3→## Key Files & Roles\n     4→\n     5→- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for agent scripts. Provides environment defaults, output helpers, cleanup/trap setup, lock handling, and shared result formatting utilities.\n     6→- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: refactored agent using the shared library; pattern for complex scoped execution and structured output.\n     7→- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: refactored single-step and multi-step domain runner with CHANGED_FILES mapping and CI-aware format behavior.\n     8→- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: refactored agent that demonstrates formatter/linter fallbacks and scoped execution over changed files.\n     9→- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: refactored agent with optional tooling (tflint), non-mutating checks, and lock-aware sequencing.\n    10→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: central test orchestrator for shellcheck plus fixture execution.\n    11→- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: per-agent scenario fixtures; each includes `scenario.env` with `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n    12→- `install.sh`: installer entrypoint; currently installs `bash-agent`, `cargo-agent`, `go-agent`, `npm-agent`, `py-agent`, and `terra-agent`, and patches shared library for local/remote install modes.\n    13→- `README.md`: human-facing agent catalog, usage examples, and quick-start guidance.\n    14→- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI currently runs scenario slices for bash, cargo, go, npm, py, and terraform agents.\n    15→- `.ralph/specs/05-gha-agent.md`: current specification for the new gha-agent implementation.\n    16→- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: reference for required files, trigger patterns, and required helpers for each new agent.\n    17→- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: final acceptance checks for any new agent.\n    18→- `.ralph/task.md`: task-level scope and spec sequence for eight remaining agents.\n    19→- `.ralph/automation-opportunities.md`: pending candidates for automatable process improvements.\n    20→- `.ralph/lessons.jsonl`: historical manual lessons and decision points."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04f1945e-7bf3-4940-ab64-46803dcd06b1","uuid":"e08fc0e9-d063-400a-919e-44edb3ce98d8","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","content":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for agent scripts. Provides environment defaults, output helpers, cleanup/trap setup, lock handling, and shared result formatting utilities.\n- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: refactored agent using the shared library; pattern for complex scoped execution and structured output.\n- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: refactored single-step and multi-step domain runner with CHANGED_FILES mapping and CI-aware format behavior.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: refactored agent that demonstrates formatter/linter fallbacks and scoped execution over changed files.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: refactored agent with optional tooling (tflint), non-mutating checks, and lock-aware sequencing.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: central test orchestrator for shellcheck plus fixture execution.\n- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: per-agent scenario fixtures; each includes `scenario.env` with `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- `install.sh`: installer entrypoint; currently installs `bash-agent`, `cargo-agent`, `go-agent`, `npm-agent`, `py-agent`, and `terra-agent`, and patches shared library for local/remote install modes.\n- `README.md`: human-facing agent catalog, usage examples, and quick-start guidance.\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI currently runs scenario slices for bash, cargo, go, npm, py, and terraform agents.\n- `.ralph/specs/05-gha-agent.md`: current specification for the new gha-agent implementation.\n- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: reference for required files, trigger patterns, and required helpers for each new agent.\n- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: final acceptance checks for any new agent.\n- `.ralph/task.md`: task-level scope and spec sequence for eight remaining agents.\n- `.ralph/automation-opportunities.md`: pending candidates for automatable process improvements.\n- `.ralph/lessons.jsonl`: historical manual lessons and decision points.","numLines":20,"startLine":1,"totalLines":56}}}
